<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-11-08T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-11-08T19:00:00-05:00" n="1069" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1069">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">838.51/4107b: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chargé in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Sparks</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-11-08T19:00:00-05:00">November 8, 1940—7
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>181. Chargé’s personal letter to Duggan<note n="53" xml:id="d1069fn1">Not
                                found in Department files.</note> and Department’s telegram 177,
                            November 1, 5 p.m. Department understands that the request of the
                            Haitian Government will be for a temporary reduction for the period of
                            this fiscal year.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>